  "body": "### Description\r\nTOML supports flat configuration properties as well as \"tables\" - sections that contain related properties. Besu does not currently support tables.\r\n\r\nLink to discussion on Discord: https://discord.com/channels/905194001349627914/905205502940696607/1110382467719893083\r\n\r\nLink to contributor call where this enhancement was discussed and agreed: https://wiki.hyperledger.org/display/BESU/2023-05-23+Contributor+Call+-+APAC+Friendly+Time\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nAs an administrator I can provide Besu with the following TOML configuration file using the `--config-file` flag:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[TxPool]\r\ntx-pool-max-size = 2048\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Besu starts correctly without errors\r\n2. TX pool max size is correctly configured to the given value\r\n3. The `[TxPool]` TOML table is ignored\r\n",
