    "body": "Fixing this is a little more complicated than I'd hoped. Getting Besu to ignore (i.e. not report as errors) table headings is relatively straight forward. But retrieving the value from a parsed TOML file is less so, because the parsed data nests the values under dotted table names.\r\n\r\ni.e. in the example in the description of the issue, to get `tx-pool-max-size` requires a call to `result.get(\"TxPool.tx-pool-max-size\")`. A call to `result.get(\"tx-pool-max-size\")` will simply return null.",
